In this article, Vice President Mike Pence speaks at the Meeting Place Church in Columbia, South Carolina. He thanks the church for their work in transforming the community and celebrates the partnership between local businesses and the church. Pence is accompanied by his wife, Karen Pence, and praises Senator Tim Scott for his leadership. Pence also brings greetings from President Donald Trump and discusses the positive impact of Opportunity Zones in creating jobs and economic growth. He commends the progress made in Columbia and emphasizes the importance of faith in building a strong foundation for community development. Pence concludes by expressing optimism for the future of Columbia, South Carolina, and the United States.